<p>Using rvm, you can install any new version of ruby using the following :</p>

<p>rvm use 1.9.3
ruby -v #=&gt; ruby 1.9.3p125 (2012-02-16 revision 34643) [x86_64-darwin12.2.0]
rvm use 2.0.0
ruby -v #=&gt; ruby 2.0.0p0 (2013-02-24 revision 39474</p>

<p>rvm install 2.0.0-p0 #=&gt; This will install Ruby 2.0.0
rvm install jruby #=&gt; This will install jruby</p>

